1
00:01:37,060 --> 00:01:40,170
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:43,150
[Episode 37]

3
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:08,960
Come back.

4
00:02:13,310 --> 00:02:14,650
Just because you tell me to

5
00:02:14,650 --> 00:02:15,780
doesn't mean I will.

6
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:17,140
You...

7
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:25,579
Bai Ju told me everything.

8
00:02:27,690 --> 00:02:28,620
What did she say?

9
00:02:29,079 --> 00:02:30,470
Something is wrong with

10
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:34,110
Hongyuan, Xinhai, and Meng Yaohui.

11
00:02:35,460 --> 00:02:37,120
It's not just illegal mining.

12
00:02:38,530 --> 00:02:40,590
There's a lot more going on with them.

13
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:45,990
I don't know how to explain it.

14
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:47,720
I was wrong, okay?

15
00:02:50,610 --> 00:02:52,410
But your words were hurtful too.

16
00:02:53,980 --> 00:02:55,980
How can you say I have no conscience?

17
00:02:57,410 --> 00:02:57,990
We've been investigating
and investigating,

18
00:02:57,990 --> 00:02:59,450
but we still know nothing.

19
00:03:00,540 --> 00:03:01,870
I just got a bit anxious.

20
00:03:02,430 --> 00:03:04,030
Can't I get angry about that?

21
00:03:05,540 --> 00:03:06,940
Didn't you get angry too?

22
00:03:07,290 --> 00:03:09,550
When you get angry, that's what's scary.

23
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:11,590
I only meant

24
00:03:12,380 --> 00:03:13,240
to lecture you.

25
00:03:13,730 --> 00:03:14,660
But what you said

26
00:03:15,420 --> 00:03:16,560
was much scarier

27
00:03:16,670 --> 00:03:17,600
than my lecture.

28
00:03:22,970 --> 00:03:23,970
You're laughing?

29
00:03:25,460 --> 00:03:26,790
You're still laughing?

30
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:31,850
How can you still laugh?

31
00:03:41,370 --> 00:03:42,960
What a scary reporter.

32
00:03:57,630 --> 00:03:59,140
So, are we good now?

33
00:04:00,090 --> 00:04:02,350
The Mountain God's steward is watching.

34
00:04:07,190 --> 00:04:08,030
You are...

35
00:04:13,170 --> 00:04:13,970
Manager Zhao.

36
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:18,850
You're from the Mountain Patrol.

37
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:25,680
The Mountain God's steward...

38
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:28,560
I've always remembered you all.

39
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:30,980
You can't mine that mountain.

40
00:04:31,290 --> 00:04:32,030
Why?

41
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:35,030
That is the Mountain God's

42
00:04:35,060 --> 00:04:36,159
third wife.

43
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:38,250
You see that one over there?

44
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:41,280
That's the Mountain God's second wife.

45
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:42,810
The mountain to the south is

46
00:04:42,810 --> 00:04:44,409
the Mountain God's steward.

47
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:49,930
It's you.

48
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:51,750
You still remember me?

49
00:04:59,330 --> 00:05:01,420
I didn't expect to meet you again.

50
00:05:01,870 --> 00:05:02,560
Yeah.

51
00:05:05,970 --> 00:05:06,740
Zhacuo.

52
00:05:09,620 --> 00:05:10,690
You were right.

53
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:13,230
Those mountains

54
00:05:14,110 --> 00:05:15,030
can't be mined.

55
00:05:25,980 --> 00:05:27,920
Ding used to tell me

56
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,720
that his fate

57
00:05:30,220 --> 00:05:31,810
clashed with the element of earth.

58
00:05:31,810 --> 00:05:32,610
That's why

59
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:34,540
he never found any ore.

60
00:05:35,250 --> 00:05:36,450
When I was young,

61
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,860
I didn't believe in fate.

62
00:05:37,860 --> 00:05:38,790
I really didn't.

63
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:40,930
But it's different now.

64
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,190
After all these years,

65
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:44,590
my mindset has changed.

66
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:47,620
I suddenly realized

67
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,120
that, for every one of us,

68
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:52,920
every step we take

69
00:05:54,180 --> 00:05:55,280
seems somehow

70
00:05:55,310 --> 00:05:57,050
destined by fate.

71
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,300
Back then,

72
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,220
if I hadn't gone down that road

73
00:06:03,220 --> 00:06:04,830
to Bolamula

74
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,430
to explore for mines...

75
00:06:09,690 --> 00:06:10,940
would everything that followed

76
00:06:10,940 --> 00:06:12,180
have happened?

77
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:14,750
What...

78
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:16,050
followed?

79
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,830
What followed was...

80
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:23,220
was everything

81
00:06:23,310 --> 00:06:25,710
you uncovered during your investigation.

82
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,890
I handed over the company

83
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:30,360
and... retired.

84
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:33,750
Who retires at such a young age?

85
00:06:36,570 --> 00:06:37,630
I'm in poor health.

86
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:40,830
I'm in poor health,

87
00:06:41,770 --> 00:06:42,810
so I had to retire.

88
00:06:44,130 --> 00:06:46,010
You look pretty healthy to me.

89
00:06:46,330 --> 00:06:47,620
You don't even need

90
00:06:47,670 --> 00:06:49,400
supplemental oxygen anymore.

91
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:51,830
Zhacuo.

92
00:06:55,330 --> 00:06:56,140
Even to this day,

93
00:06:56,140 --> 00:06:57,790
I can't believe

94
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,950
we still have the chance

95
00:06:59,980 --> 00:07:01,620
to have a meal together.

96
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:05,610
After this meal,

97
00:07:05,610 --> 00:07:06,610
you should leave.

98
00:07:07,830 --> 00:07:08,510
Don't

99
00:07:09,010 --> 00:07:10,010
come see me again.

100
00:07:11,310 --> 00:07:13,440
We didn't come here for anything else.

101
00:07:14,420 --> 00:07:15,750
If you want,

102
00:07:16,420 --> 00:07:17,480
next time we can bring along

103
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:18,350
other former Mountain Patrol members

104
00:07:18,350 --> 00:07:19,340
to visit you.

105
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:22,620
Next time...

106
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:29,330
I don't dare promise anything

107
00:07:29,330 --> 00:07:30,530
about the future now.

108
00:07:31,950 --> 00:07:33,270
I might not even

109
00:07:34,770 --> 00:07:36,260
make it to next year.

110
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:45,710
Auntie,

111
00:07:45,740 --> 00:07:46,570
please count it again.

112
00:07:46,570 --> 00:07:48,390
Check whether the money's all there.

113
00:07:48,390 --> 00:07:49,020
No.

114
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:49,960
It's all here.

115
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:51,600
Bai,

116
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:53,220
thank you so much.

117
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:54,230
You're welcome.

118
00:07:55,050 --> 00:07:55,890
What about that man?

119
00:07:55,890 --> 00:07:56,890
Did you catch him?

120
00:07:58,870 --> 00:08:00,510
We caught him,

121
00:08:00,620 --> 00:08:02,250
but as for visitation...

122
00:08:02,810 --> 00:08:03,620
Good!

123
00:08:04,250 --> 00:08:04,720
People like him

124
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:05,950
belong in prison!

125
00:08:06,250 --> 00:08:07,830
If you don't teach him a lesson,

126
00:08:07,830 --> 00:08:09,470
he'll keep scamming people.

127
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,770
You've thought it through?

128
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:15,390
Yeah, I have!

129
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:18,250
It's just that I caused too much trouble

130
00:08:18,250 --> 00:08:19,890
for you police officers.

131
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:20,830
It's fine.

132
00:08:21,220 --> 00:08:22,080
Let me show you.

133
00:08:23,110 --> 00:08:23,950
This is

134
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:25,170
my new boyfriend.

135
00:08:25,620 --> 00:08:26,390
What do you think?

136
00:08:26,390 --> 00:08:27,790
Pretty handsome, right?

137
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,120
Look.

138
00:08:32,890 --> 00:08:33,610
Auntie,

139
00:08:33,710 --> 00:08:35,830
this photo looks a bit...

140
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,130
Looks a bit fake.

141
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,049
Don't worry.

142
00:08:39,370 --> 00:08:40,150
This time,

143
00:08:40,250 --> 00:08:41,630
I'll just give him my affection.

144
00:08:41,630 --> 00:08:42,210
I definitely

145
00:08:42,210 --> 00:08:43,809
won't let him take any money.

146
00:08:44,820 --> 00:08:45,950
Besides,

147
00:08:46,410 --> 00:08:47,670
now I have you

148
00:08:47,690 --> 00:08:48,770
by my side, don't I?

149
00:08:52,460 --> 00:08:53,460
Although I'm terrible at

150
00:08:53,460 --> 00:08:54,340
judging men,

151
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:56,520
I'm very good at reading women.

152
00:08:56,620 --> 00:08:58,010
I could tell at first glance

153
00:08:58,010 --> 00:08:59,340
that you're a good girl.

154
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:02,440
Yaohui, my child,

155
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:03,430
over the years,

156
00:09:03,430 --> 00:09:04,890
has offended many people.

157
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:07,100
He's hardly made any real friends,

158
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:09,320
and he especially doesn't trust women.

159
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:10,550
But I can feel it.

160
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,730
He treats you differently.

161
00:09:15,410 --> 00:09:16,120
Auntie,

162
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:19,910
actually, you've misunderstood.

163
00:09:19,910 --> 00:09:21,240
Mr. Meng and I...

164
00:09:21,340 --> 00:09:21,840
I...

165
00:09:24,270 --> 00:09:25,800
Let me peel an apple for you.

166
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:27,620
I'll get a knife.

167
00:09:27,620 --> 00:09:27,960
Wait here for a sec.

168
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:29,220
Don't bother, Auntie!

169
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:57,700
Yaohui gave me this

170
00:09:57,700 --> 00:09:58,760
as a birthday gift.

171
00:09:58,870 --> 00:10:00,460
I was born in the Year of the Ox.

172
00:10:00,460 --> 00:10:01,530
He said this elephant

173
00:10:01,530 --> 00:10:03,080
has eyes like an ox.

174
00:10:03,790 --> 00:10:05,430
I can't really tell though.

175
00:10:07,390 --> 00:10:08,220
He

176
00:10:08,650 --> 00:10:10,110
seems cold on the outside,

177
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:11,000
but he's

178
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:12,360
actually warm inside.

179
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:14,220
He really values relationships.

180
00:10:15,010 --> 00:10:16,960
I'm not trying to set you up.

181
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:19,410
I just hope that when it really matters,

182
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:20,220
you can give him a hand

183
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:21,130
like a friend.

184
00:10:21,550 --> 00:10:22,790
That's all I ask.

185
00:10:24,980 --> 00:10:25,650
Auntie,

186
00:10:26,010 --> 00:10:27,120
this elephant's design

187
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:28,500
is pretty unique.

188
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:29,660
Where did he get it?

189
00:10:29,910 --> 00:10:30,600
Guangzhou.

190
00:10:32,330 --> 00:10:33,590
Where did you buy this?

191
00:10:33,930 --> 00:10:35,080
I brought it back from my road trip

192
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:36,010
to South Asia.

193
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:37,600
Shao, if you like it,

194
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,260
it's yours.

195
00:10:52,530 --> 00:10:53,740
Meng Yaohui

196
00:10:53,940 --> 00:10:55,790
really does have a strange taste

197
00:10:55,830 --> 00:10:56,940
in gifts.

198
00:10:58,410 --> 00:11:01,030
He takes after his father—practical.

199
00:11:01,550 --> 00:11:02,770
He didn't inherit

200
00:11:02,790 --> 00:11:05,090
any of my romantic genes.

201
00:11:05,820 --> 00:11:07,220
Being practical is good.

202
00:11:08,830 --> 00:11:09,610
Auntie,

203
00:11:09,650 --> 00:11:10,200
when did he

204
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,530
give you this elephant?

205
00:11:11,820 --> 00:11:12,670
1997.

206
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,000
My zodiac year.

207
00:11:18,170 --> 00:11:18,830
That year,

208
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:20,320
something big did happen.

209
00:11:21,130 --> 00:11:22,330
Yaohui had a breakup.

210
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:24,620
He said he didn't want to
stay in Tianduo anymore

211
00:11:24,620 --> 00:11:25,460
and wanted to go somewhere else

212
00:11:25,460 --> 00:11:26,790
for a change of scenery.

213
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:29,080
The way he was back then,

214
00:11:29,170 --> 00:11:29,670
I thought

215
00:11:29,670 --> 00:11:30,600
he'd settle down in the south

216
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,840
and never come back.

217
00:11:33,870 --> 00:11:35,400
Didn't you ever think about

218
00:11:35,410 --> 00:11:37,030
going to Guangzhou to see him,

219
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:38,010
or maybe

220
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:39,580
going with him at the time?

221
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:42,630
I... I had just gotten married
at that time

222
00:11:42,630 --> 00:11:43,760
and couldn't leave.

223
00:11:44,420 --> 00:11:45,370
Besides,

224
00:11:45,630 --> 00:11:46,820
the south might be nice,

225
00:11:46,820 --> 00:11:48,550
but it's not as good as Tianduo.

226
00:11:48,630 --> 00:11:50,230
It's my hometown, after all.

227
00:11:50,940 --> 00:11:51,650
True.

228
00:11:51,870 --> 00:11:53,460
You've been in Tianduo a long time.

229
00:11:53,460 --> 00:11:54,600
That's right.

230
00:11:55,270 --> 00:11:56,370
Like... uh...

231
00:11:56,710 --> 00:11:57,460
Mazhi,

232
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:58,190
Dingduo,

233
00:11:58,270 --> 00:11:58,910
Dongxiang—

234
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:00,360
I lived in all those places
when I was younger.

235
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:01,890
I know those counties well.

236
00:12:01,910 --> 00:12:02,630
Really?

237
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:04,840
Auntie,

238
00:12:04,870 --> 00:12:05,790
can you help me

239
00:12:05,810 --> 00:12:07,940
look through some photos of suspects?

240
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:09,750
Me? Can I?

241
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:11,460
Does it have anything to do with me?

242
00:12:11,460 --> 00:12:12,170
It has nothing to do with you.

243
00:12:12,170 --> 00:12:13,170
Don't be nervous.

244
00:12:13,570 --> 00:12:14,170
I just

245
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:16,100
want you to help identify someone.

246
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:17,320
After all, some of the cases

247
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:19,530
are about to reach
the statute of limitations.

248
00:12:19,530 --> 00:12:20,510
I was thinking,

249
00:12:20,620 --> 00:12:21,860
since you've been all over Tianduo,

250
00:12:21,860 --> 00:12:22,870
lived everywhere,

251
00:12:22,870 --> 00:12:24,200
and know a lot of people,

252
00:12:24,460 --> 00:12:25,630
you could help me recall—

253
00:12:25,630 --> 00:12:26,240
maybe,

254
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:27,980
just maybe, you'll remember some clues.

255
00:12:27,980 --> 00:12:29,060
Please take a look for me.

256
00:12:29,060 --> 00:12:30,300
Okay, okay.

257
00:12:30,560 --> 00:12:31,730
Then, let me...

258
00:12:31,910 --> 00:12:32,720
let me get my glasses.

259
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:33,120
Okay.

260
00:12:33,220 --> 00:12:34,790
Any small detail will do.

261
00:12:35,270 --> 00:12:36,460
If you recognize someone, great,

262
00:12:36,460 --> 00:12:38,390
but it doesn't matter if you can't.

263
00:12:38,510 --> 00:12:39,630
There are five photos in total.

264
00:12:39,630 --> 00:12:40,460
Take your time.

265
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:40,990
Alright.

266
00:12:42,670 --> 00:12:43,870
I don't know this one.

267
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:48,430
This one is actually kind of handsome.

268
00:12:48,830 --> 00:12:49,270
Back then,

269
00:12:49,270 --> 00:12:50,360
if he looked like this in a photo,

270
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:52,050
he must have been
even better-looking in person.

271
00:12:52,050 --> 00:12:53,290
If I had seen him,

272
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,700
I definitely wouldn't have forgotten.

273
00:12:57,130 --> 00:12:57,790
This one...

274
00:12:58,390 --> 00:12:59,860
This one looks like a colleague of mine

275
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:00,990
from back in the day.

276
00:13:01,890 --> 00:13:03,550
But that colleague of mine...

277
00:13:03,860 --> 00:13:05,100
was a bit bald.

278
00:13:07,740 --> 00:13:08,200
This...

279
00:13:11,050 --> 00:13:11,530
Um...

280
00:13:12,220 --> 00:13:12,880
This one...

281
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,050
This... This one is way too blurry.

282
00:13:16,050 --> 00:13:17,180
I can't see clearly.

283
00:13:17,740 --> 00:13:19,600
No wonder you can't catch the guy.

284
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:21,060
Bai,

285
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:21,930
I'm really sorry.

286
00:13:21,930 --> 00:13:23,060
I couldn't help you.

287
00:13:23,130 --> 00:13:23,860
It's okay, Auntie.

288
00:13:23,860 --> 00:13:25,360
I was just trying my luck.

289
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:28,050
Thank you, Auntie.

290
00:13:28,050 --> 00:13:28,510
Okay.

291
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,860
Wang Fumin is the victim?

292
00:13:36,310 --> 00:13:37,510
Do you have evidence?

293
00:13:37,670 --> 00:13:38,480
Not yet.

294
00:13:40,180 --> 00:13:40,940
Previously, based on

295
00:13:40,940 --> 00:13:42,270
the skeletal analysis,

296
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:44,580
we speculated that the body was Duojie.

297
00:13:44,580 --> 00:13:46,410
Among the items left at the scene,

298
00:13:46,410 --> 00:13:47,600
we found some physical evidence

299
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:48,660
left by the killer.

300
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:50,390
Based on that evidence, we inferred

301
00:13:50,390 --> 00:13:51,410
that the missing employee
from Hongyuan Freight Company,

302
00:13:51,410 --> 00:13:52,910
Wang Fumin,

303
00:13:53,010 --> 00:13:54,940
was the suspect who killed Duojie.

304
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:56,480
According to our investigation,

305
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:57,190
Wang Fumin

306
00:13:57,220 --> 00:13:57,960
went abroad to work

307
00:13:57,960 --> 00:13:58,980
17 years ago

308
00:13:59,010 --> 00:14:00,870
and hasn't been heard from since.

309
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:01,990
It looks like

310
00:14:02,050 --> 00:14:03,710
he fled to escape punishment.

311
00:14:04,690 --> 00:14:05,130
But isn't there

312
00:14:05,130 --> 00:14:06,390
another possibility?

313
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:07,960
You mean...

314
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:10,150
Wang Fumin was killed?

315
00:14:10,490 --> 00:14:10,990
Yes.

316
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:14,240
There's no record of him abroad,

317
00:14:14,890 --> 00:14:15,820
possibly because

318
00:14:15,820 --> 00:14:17,220
he never left the country

319
00:14:18,010 --> 00:14:19,180
and was buried in the wilderness

320
00:14:19,180 --> 00:14:20,190
for 17 years.

321
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:22,500
Also,

322
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:24,250
based on the photos we obtained

323
00:14:24,250 --> 00:14:25,790
and our questioning of the family,

324
00:14:25,790 --> 00:14:26,620
his build

325
00:14:27,060 --> 00:14:28,390
is similar to Duojie's.

326
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:29,630
Moreover,

327
00:14:30,250 --> 00:14:31,640
since Meng's mother could recognize

328
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:32,300
Wang Fumin,

329
00:14:32,770 --> 00:14:33,580
I suspect Meng Yaohui

330
00:14:33,580 --> 00:14:34,580
is also connected

331
00:14:34,820 --> 00:14:35,620
to Wang Fumin.

332
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:36,670
Then we need to verify

333
00:14:36,670 --> 00:14:38,130
this theory of yours ASAP.

334
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:39,120
Contact

335
00:14:39,150 --> 00:14:40,430
Wang Fumin's son immediately

336
00:14:40,430 --> 00:14:42,430
and collect his DNA for comparison.

337
00:14:45,010 --> 00:14:45,750
Hello?

338
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:47,250
Is anyone there?

339
00:14:48,650 --> 00:14:49,270
Wang Jian!

340
00:14:49,370 --> 00:14:50,080
Wang Jian!

341
00:14:51,170 --> 00:14:51,860
Wang Jian?

342
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:52,670
Hello?

343
00:14:53,530 --> 00:14:54,460
Are you here to collect a debt

344
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:56,140
for yourself or on someone else's behalf?

345
00:14:56,140 --> 00:14:57,070
What did you say?

346
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:00,920
Police!

347
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:02,810
We are police officers.

348
00:15:02,910 --> 00:15:04,260
We'd like to ask you a few questions.

349
00:15:04,260 --> 00:15:06,190
Will you please cooperate with us?

350
00:15:06,870 --> 00:15:08,470
Oh, you're police officers.

351
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:09,480
I thought

352
00:15:09,530 --> 00:15:11,530
you were the debt collectors again.

353
00:15:12,340 --> 00:15:13,270
Does Wang Jian

354
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:14,460
owe money?

355
00:15:14,550 --> 00:15:16,150
He moved out because of his debts.

356
00:15:16,150 --> 00:15:17,860
He claimed his startup failed,

357
00:15:17,860 --> 00:15:19,560
but actually, he loved
buying lottery tickets

358
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:21,620
and hoped to strike it rich every day.

359
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:22,830
When did he move out?

360
00:15:23,550 --> 00:15:24,950
Do you know where he went?

361
00:15:25,030 --> 00:15:26,340
Just a while ago.

362
00:15:26,370 --> 00:15:28,020
After the police came looking for him,

363
00:15:28,020 --> 00:15:28,640
he packed up

364
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:29,640
in a real hurry

365
00:15:29,690 --> 00:15:30,620
a few days later.

366
00:15:30,620 --> 00:15:31,870
Didn't say where he was going either.

367
00:15:31,870 --> 00:15:32,610
Just loaded

368
00:15:32,630 --> 00:15:33,840
some luggage into a van.

369
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:35,440
He left a lot of stuff behind.

370
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:38,700
Thank you, sir.

371
00:15:38,940 --> 00:15:40,070
Sorry to bother you.

372
00:15:54,410 --> 00:15:54,910
Mom.

373
00:15:56,870 --> 00:15:58,240
You're back so late.

374
00:15:59,340 --> 00:16:00,200
Have you eaten?

375
00:16:00,410 --> 00:16:00,950
I have.

376
00:16:01,510 --> 00:16:02,170
You have?

377
00:16:04,510 --> 00:16:05,510
You didn't drink?

378
00:16:05,860 --> 00:16:07,320
No business dinner today.

379
00:16:07,860 --> 00:16:09,720
I went to Dongxiang for some work.

380
00:16:11,410 --> 00:16:13,010
You went to Dongxiang again?

381
00:16:14,510 --> 00:16:15,240
I made a pot of tea.

382
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,100
Come have a cup.

383
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:21,980
Freshly brewed.

384
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:27,140
I need to take this.

385
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:29,150
Hello?

386
00:16:30,270 --> 00:16:31,480
Don't push your luck.

387
00:16:32,310 --> 00:16:34,040
I said I can't give you any more.

388
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:36,000
Leave immediately.

389
00:16:37,660 --> 00:16:39,750
I'll give you an apartment in Dingduo.

390
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:40,950
Once you get there...

391
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:42,580
Once you get there,

392
00:16:42,580 --> 00:16:43,910
you'll get another one.

393
00:16:59,570 --> 00:17:00,340
Auntie.

394
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:01,460
Bai,

395
00:17:02,050 --> 00:17:02,840
what's up?

396
00:17:03,590 --> 00:17:04,609
Nothing big.

397
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:05,849
I just wanted to ask

398
00:17:06,420 --> 00:17:07,069
if Yaohui has been

399
00:17:07,069 --> 00:17:08,660
very busy these past few days.

400
00:17:08,660 --> 00:17:09,770
It seems so.

401
00:17:10,839 --> 00:17:11,359
Why?

402
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:12,349
Have things not been

403
00:17:12,349 --> 00:17:14,280
going well between you two lately?

404
00:17:15,250 --> 00:17:16,050
Yeah.

405
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:17,950
I've been texting him
these past couple of days,

406
00:17:17,950 --> 00:17:20,050
and he hasn't been responding
very quickly.

407
00:17:20,050 --> 00:17:20,589
I don't know

408
00:17:20,589 --> 00:17:21,990
what he's been busy with.

409
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:23,810
Now that you mention it,

410
00:17:23,940 --> 00:17:24,849
I feel

411
00:17:25,510 --> 00:17:26,200
he's been acting

412
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,599
a bit strange lately too.

413
00:17:27,829 --> 00:17:28,750
Really?

414
00:17:29,470 --> 00:17:30,750
What's going on with him?

415
00:17:30,750 --> 00:17:31,610
Yaohui has been

416
00:17:31,660 --> 00:17:33,320
acting all secretive lately.

417
00:17:33,750 --> 00:17:34,880
When I asked where he went,

418
00:17:34,880 --> 00:17:35,880
he even lied to me,

419
00:17:36,250 --> 00:17:37,730
saying he went to Dongxiang.

420
00:17:37,730 --> 00:17:39,190
He went there again today.

421
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:40,380
After he came back,

422
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:42,500
he was on the phone on the balcony,

423
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:43,720
saying something about

424
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:45,120
an apartment in Dingduo.

425
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:48,550
He might have another woman in Dingduo.

426
00:17:48,550 --> 00:17:49,480
But don't worry.

427
00:17:49,690 --> 00:17:51,320
I'm on your side.

428
00:17:52,420 --> 00:17:53,610
I know, Auntie.

429
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:54,760
Please help me

430
00:17:54,790 --> 00:17:55,810
keep an eye on him.

431
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:57,300
No problem.

432
00:17:57,610 --> 00:17:58,680
Leave it to me.

433
00:17:59,370 --> 00:18:00,830
I'll hang up then, Auntie.

434
00:18:18,530 --> 00:18:19,460
Enjoy your meal.

435
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:29,180
So

436
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:30,280
if I hadn't called,

437
00:18:31,050 --> 00:18:32,330
you still wouldn't have come to see me?

438
00:18:32,330 --> 00:18:33,030
No.

439
00:18:37,160 --> 00:18:37,740
Shao.

440
00:18:39,770 --> 00:18:40,420
I'm sorry.

441
00:18:41,660 --> 00:18:43,120
I've realized something.

442
00:18:44,270 --> 00:18:45,150
You

443
00:18:45,180 --> 00:18:46,440
Mountain Patrol folks

444
00:18:46,830 --> 00:18:47,890
are all pretty passive

445
00:18:47,890 --> 00:18:49,690
when it comes to relationships.

446
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:51,820
I just thought

447
00:18:51,850 --> 00:18:52,980
you were still mad.

448
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,700
Ji is definitely still mad.

449
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:57,560
That's why I'm playing peacemaker here.

450
00:18:59,350 --> 00:19:00,810
So you're not mad anymore?

451
00:19:01,610 --> 00:19:02,370
You might not

452
00:19:02,500 --> 00:19:03,630
get your money back.

453
00:19:03,860 --> 00:19:05,950
If getting angry paid off,

454
00:19:06,110 --> 00:19:07,700
I'd do it every day.

455
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:15,040
Visit Mom when you have time.

456
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:16,230
I only came to see you

457
00:19:16,230 --> 00:19:17,050
for her sake.

458
00:19:17,390 --> 00:19:18,330
What's wrong with Mom?

459
00:19:18,330 --> 00:19:20,190
You and Ji are fighting like this.

460
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:22,590
And Chun has been missing for days too.

461
00:19:22,590 --> 00:19:24,500
We finally reached him by phone that day,

462
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:24,940
but we don't know

463
00:19:24,940 --> 00:19:26,230
if it was bad reception in the mines

464
00:19:26,230 --> 00:19:27,010
or what—

465
00:19:27,410 --> 00:19:29,420
he just said he didn't wanna do it anymore

466
00:19:29,420 --> 00:19:30,820
and hung up immediately.

467
00:19:31,510 --> 00:19:31,940
Do you know

468
00:19:31,940 --> 00:19:33,000
how worried Mom is?

469
00:19:36,190 --> 00:19:37,320
That's all I'll say.

470
00:19:38,390 --> 00:19:39,790
Act a little more mature.

471
00:19:41,770 --> 00:19:42,830
And another thing.

472
00:19:43,940 --> 00:19:44,800
Did you

473
00:19:44,830 --> 00:19:46,000
block me on Moments?

474
00:19:47,420 --> 00:19:48,220
No, I didn't.

475
00:19:48,270 --> 00:19:50,130
You're accusing me wrongly here.

476
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:51,010
Look.

477
00:19:51,870 --> 00:19:53,340
I haven't posted anything on Moments.

478
00:19:53,340 --> 00:19:53,770
Look.

479
00:19:55,220 --> 00:19:55,810
That's right!

480
00:19:55,810 --> 00:19:56,250
I haven't seen

481
00:19:56,250 --> 00:19:57,650
a single update from you!

482
00:19:57,850 --> 00:19:58,200
I don't know

483
00:19:58,200 --> 00:19:59,500
what you've been up to lately!

484
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:00,530
So what can I do?

485
00:20:03,290 --> 00:20:05,010
Look at Alex—

486
00:20:05,410 --> 00:20:07,070
he posts on Moments every day.

487
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:08,870
W-Who is Alex?

488
00:20:13,220 --> 00:20:14,200
Who is he?

489
00:20:14,420 --> 00:20:15,270
Do I know him?

490
00:20:17,620 --> 00:20:18,600
Lin Jianshe.

491
00:20:22,030 --> 00:20:23,220
This is Lin Jianshe?

492
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:24,000
How...

493
00:20:24,870 --> 00:20:25,410
How...

494
00:20:25,530 --> 00:20:26,740
how did he change so much?

495
00:20:26,740 --> 00:20:27,180
He looks like

496
00:20:27,180 --> 00:20:28,510
he's been inflated or something.

497
00:20:28,510 --> 00:20:29,170
He's so fat.

498
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:30,080
He's

499
00:20:30,110 --> 00:20:32,000
living the good life abroad now.

500
00:20:32,220 --> 00:20:33,030
I heard

501
00:20:33,550 --> 00:20:34,200
he even married

502
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,420
a foreign wife.

503
00:20:35,550 --> 00:20:36,290
Really?

504
00:20:40,370 --> 00:20:41,220
He's certainly

505
00:20:41,220 --> 00:20:42,350
doing quite well.

506
00:20:45,640 --> 00:20:45,910
But

507
00:20:45,930 --> 00:20:47,390
how do you have his WeChat?

508
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:48,700
Back when we started using WeChat,

509
00:20:48,700 --> 00:20:50,070
wasn't there a feature

510
00:20:50,180 --> 00:20:51,330
that recommended friends

511
00:20:51,330 --> 00:20:52,830
from your contacts?

512
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:54,960
He added me.

513
00:20:56,610 --> 00:20:57,570
Why did he add you?

514
00:20:57,570 --> 00:20:58,390
To show off.

515
00:20:58,420 --> 00:20:59,240
Why else?

516
00:20:59,270 --> 00:21:00,460
He obviously wanted to flaunt it,

517
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:01,240
like, "Look at me, I'm abroad now,

518
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:02,640
living it up."

519
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:03,330
I'm telling you,

520
00:21:03,330 --> 00:21:04,050
my Moments feed

521
00:21:04,050 --> 00:21:04,880
is full of people like that.

522
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:06,000
One more or one less

523
00:21:06,020 --> 00:21:07,220
makes no difference.

524
00:21:19,110 --> 00:21:20,770
How does Lin Jianshe know him?

525
00:21:21,580 --> 00:21:22,220
Who?

526
00:21:25,110 --> 00:21:25,720
Let me see.

527
00:21:28,570 --> 00:21:29,370
What are you doing?

528
00:21:29,370 --> 00:21:30,740
Who are you sending that to?

529
00:21:30,740 --> 00:21:31,380
Don't mess around.

530
00:21:31,380 --> 00:21:31,680
No, no.

531
00:21:31,680 --> 00:21:32,220
I'm not sending it to anyone.

532
00:21:32,220 --> 00:21:33,620
I'm sending it to myself.

533
00:21:33,850 --> 00:21:34,510
Okay, sent.

534
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:34,960
Look.

535
00:21:34,980 --> 00:21:36,240
Why did you send this photo to yourself?

536
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:37,220
Who is this?

537
00:21:38,420 --> 00:21:39,180
No one.

538
00:21:45,690 --> 00:21:47,270
[Xinhai Coal Mine]

539
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:05,590
Chun?

540
00:22:08,010 --> 00:22:08,680
Chun!

541
00:22:22,110 --> 00:22:24,010
Chun, are you there?

542
00:22:25,420 --> 00:22:26,350
I'm coming in.

543
00:22:36,350 --> 00:22:37,510
I haven't been able to

544
00:22:37,510 --> 00:22:39,570
reach him these past few days either.

545
00:22:39,700 --> 00:22:40,270
But I think

546
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:42,090
he really needs some rest.

547
00:22:42,460 --> 00:22:43,380
What happened?

548
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:45,910
The regreening work has probably

549
00:22:45,910 --> 00:22:47,440
put a lot of pressure on him.

550
00:22:47,850 --> 00:22:48,330
Fortunately,

551
00:22:48,330 --> 00:22:48,830
the inspection team

552
00:22:48,830 --> 00:22:50,890
is quite satisfied with our results.

553
00:22:52,170 --> 00:22:53,300
Then where did he go?

554
00:22:53,780 --> 00:22:55,260
He didn't tell me that,

555
00:22:55,460 --> 00:22:56,390
and I didn't ask.

556
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:58,420
It works out, actually.

557
00:22:58,420 --> 00:22:59,310
He hasn't really

558
00:22:59,310 --> 00:23:01,500
taken any annual leave
these past few years.

559
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:03,430
I'll treat this as making up for it.

560
00:23:09,740 --> 00:23:13,710
[Staff Cafeteria]

561
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:18,400
-Mr. Meng.
-Mr. Meng.

562
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:21,090
Mr. Meng.

563
00:23:21,590 --> 00:23:22,240
Mr. Meng.

564
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:24,100
Thank you

565
00:23:24,290 --> 00:23:25,950
for giving the money to my mom.

566
00:23:27,590 --> 00:23:29,050
It came out of your own pocket.

567
00:23:29,050 --> 00:23:30,450
It was your money anyway.

568
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:32,050
But

569
00:23:32,070 --> 00:23:33,250
you gave her the money

570
00:23:33,250 --> 00:23:34,350
as a police officer.

571
00:23:34,350 --> 00:23:34,940
It made her believe

572
00:23:34,940 --> 00:23:37,000
that the money was really recovered.

573
00:23:37,330 --> 00:23:38,680
That idea was brilliant.

574
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:39,680
She actually moved on from all that

575
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:40,750
a long time ago.

576
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:43,210
Don't you know she already has

577
00:23:43,210 --> 00:23:44,250
a new boyfriend?

578
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:47,550
Mr. Meng.

579
00:23:52,840 --> 00:23:53,900
Me and my big mouth.

580
00:23:54,480 --> 00:23:55,790
Just pretend I didn't say that,

581
00:23:55,790 --> 00:23:57,390
and you don't know anything.

582
00:23:58,800 --> 00:23:59,870
Your mom probably

583
00:24:00,540 --> 00:24:01,160
just wants you to

584
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:02,440
care more about her

585
00:24:02,990 --> 00:24:04,590
and spend more time with her.

586
00:24:06,070 --> 00:24:07,180
Oh, my mom—

587
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:09,500
why does she tell you everything?

588
00:24:12,770 --> 00:24:14,230
Things she should've said

589
00:24:14,390 --> 00:24:16,250
and things she shouldn't have...

590
00:24:16,770 --> 00:24:17,900
she said a whole lot.

591
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:26,530
She said something

592
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:27,770
she shouldn't have?

593
00:24:29,940 --> 00:24:30,810
She said...

594
00:24:33,320 --> 00:24:34,580
you don't trust women.

595
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:36,220
Is that something she should

596
00:24:36,220 --> 00:24:37,550
or shouldn't have said?

597
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:42,440
What's wrong?

598
00:24:43,030 --> 00:24:44,560
What did you think she said?

599
00:24:48,250 --> 00:24:48,810
Nothing.

600
00:24:53,240 --> 00:24:53,770
Mr. Meng,

601
00:24:53,820 --> 00:24:54,770
here's your takeaway.

602
00:24:54,770 --> 00:24:55,380
Thanks.

603
00:25:17,140 --> 00:25:18,400
You're still not full?

604
00:25:25,770 --> 00:25:27,430
People really are different.

605
00:25:29,050 --> 00:25:30,630
Back when I went into the mountains
with the team,

606
00:25:30,630 --> 00:25:31,830
I ate so much of this I swore

607
00:25:31,830 --> 00:25:33,230
I'd never touch it again.

608
00:25:34,510 --> 00:25:35,910
It's okay if you toast it.

609
00:25:36,070 --> 00:25:37,130
But cold like this,

610
00:25:37,480 --> 00:25:38,340
it's terrible.

611
00:25:38,590 --> 00:25:40,450
I think it's pretty good, though.

612
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:41,740
Back in the day...

613
00:25:44,310 --> 00:25:45,710
this is what I used to eat.

614
00:25:49,220 --> 00:25:50,220
A few days ago,

615
00:25:50,330 --> 00:25:52,060
I went to see your old teammate,

616
00:25:52,850 --> 00:25:53,590
the herder.

617
00:25:55,660 --> 00:25:56,290
I know.

618
00:25:57,140 --> 00:25:58,500
I still hope you all can

619
00:25:58,810 --> 00:26:00,160
seriously

620
00:26:00,370 --> 00:26:01,330
think about it.

621
00:26:02,870 --> 00:26:03,610
Sometimes,

622
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:05,340
when people get stuck in the past

623
00:26:05,340 --> 00:26:06,940
or trapped by an obsession,

624
00:26:07,250 --> 00:26:08,910
they just can't move forward.

625
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:26,240
Bai Ju.

626
00:26:27,550 --> 00:26:28,610
You've been to

627
00:26:28,630 --> 00:26:29,960
Bolamula so many times,

628
00:26:30,540 --> 00:26:31,390
and you've been through

629
00:26:31,390 --> 00:26:32,340
so much.

630
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,770
Have you ever thought about

631
00:26:35,010 --> 00:26:36,270
just living well?

632
00:26:37,680 --> 00:26:39,390
What counts as "living well"?

633
00:26:41,310 --> 00:26:42,250
Moving on

634
00:26:43,010 --> 00:26:44,160
and choosing

635
00:26:44,180 --> 00:26:45,380
an easier path

636
00:26:46,380 --> 00:26:47,710
instead of a lonely one.

637
00:26:56,940 --> 00:26:57,720
You've been in the Mountain Patrol

638
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:59,180
for over a year now, right?

639
00:27:01,270 --> 00:27:03,000
It's been a year and ten months.

640
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:07,480
No.

641
00:27:14,050 --> 00:27:15,200
Think again.

642
00:27:26,150 --> 00:27:27,220
It's been 18 years

643
00:27:28,330 --> 00:27:29,350
and 10 months.

644
00:27:34,260 --> 00:27:36,720
That really has been a long, long time.

645
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:41,990
You've been gone for 17 years

646
00:27:41,990 --> 00:27:43,120
and never came back.

647
00:27:48,420 --> 00:27:49,280
I'm almost

648
00:27:49,310 --> 00:27:50,550
as old as you now.

649
00:27:56,700 --> 00:27:58,220
You've just matured.

650
00:28:02,500 --> 00:28:03,180
Have I?

651
00:28:08,010 --> 00:28:09,400
But a lot of the time,

652
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:14,030
I'm still the same as before—

653
00:28:16,530 --> 00:28:17,440
not knowing if

654
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:20,550
what I'm doing now

655
00:28:20,570 --> 00:28:21,480
is right.

656
00:28:24,620 --> 00:28:26,400
Just like in Bolamula,

657
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:30,550
not knowing whether to

658
00:28:30,550 --> 00:28:32,750
keep following the path I chose.

659
00:28:35,320 --> 00:28:36,300
If I keep going,

660
00:28:39,650 --> 00:28:41,300
is home waiting ahead...

661
00:28:44,310 --> 00:28:46,010
or just deeper desolation?

662
00:28:56,980 --> 00:28:57,980
What do you think?

663
00:30:06,330 --> 00:30:07,400
Not home yet?

664
00:30:08,130 --> 00:30:09,310
Be careful on the road.

665
00:30:09,310 --> 00:30:10,910
Call me if you need anything.

666
00:30:15,790 --> 00:30:16,520
You're home,

667
00:30:16,740 --> 00:30:18,340
but I didn't want to wake you.

668
00:31:11,570 --> 00:31:12,400
It feels like after all these years,

669
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:14,000
it really hasn't grown much.

670
00:31:14,090 --> 00:31:15,240
Do you think

671
00:31:15,310 --> 00:31:16,030
we should give it

672
00:31:16,030 --> 00:31:17,630
some more fertilizer, Chun?

673
00:31:20,700 --> 00:31:22,160
How did you know I was here?

674
00:31:24,770 --> 00:31:26,480
Because this is our home.

675
00:31:27,960 --> 00:31:29,220
Where else could you go

676
00:31:29,700 --> 00:31:30,850
besides here?

677
00:31:36,850 --> 00:31:37,460
Look up.

678
00:31:38,330 --> 00:31:39,010
What for?

679
00:31:39,460 --> 00:31:40,450
Send it to Mom

680
00:31:40,480 --> 00:31:41,540
so she won't worry.

681
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:44,570
She was afraid something happened to me,

682
00:31:44,570 --> 00:31:46,500
so she asked you to come check on me?

683
00:31:47,690 --> 00:31:49,560
She didn't ask.

684
00:31:50,960 --> 00:31:52,380
I wanted to come myself.

685
00:31:59,810 --> 00:32:01,240
While you were away,

686
00:32:01,830 --> 00:32:03,630
something big happened at home.

687
00:32:05,220 --> 00:32:06,080
What happened?

688
00:32:08,140 --> 00:32:09,400
I feel that my presence

689
00:32:10,420 --> 00:32:12,160
is the greatest comfort

690
00:32:12,920 --> 00:32:14,380
and encouragement to you.

691
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:15,940
Because

692
00:32:16,110 --> 00:32:17,240
having you by my side

693
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:20,130
is the greatest comfort for me too.

694
00:32:22,530 --> 00:32:23,860
What exactly happened?

695
00:32:27,510 --> 00:32:29,110
I had a fight with Bai Ji.

696
00:32:32,500 --> 00:32:34,570
He's never been able to out-argue you
since childhood.

697
00:32:34,570 --> 00:32:36,100
What was it about this time?

698
00:32:36,320 --> 00:32:37,640
You really are a worrier.

699
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:39,240
Take care of yourself first.

700
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:44,700
What have you been doing,

701
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:47,300
staying here alone all this time?

702
00:32:50,050 --> 00:32:50,920
Nothing much.

703
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:54,200
Just thinking about what I could do.

704
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:56,060
But even if I'd done something...

705
00:32:57,470 --> 00:32:57,960
it would've felt like

706
00:32:57,960 --> 00:32:59,290
I'd done nothing at all.

707
00:33:03,940 --> 00:33:05,770
Have you been practicing tongue twisters?

708
00:33:05,770 --> 00:33:06,250
Yes.

709
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:12,220
When Dad

710
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:13,660
planted this tree,

711
00:33:15,250 --> 00:33:17,250
we all thought it wouldn't survive.

712
00:33:17,510 --> 00:33:18,530
Who would have thought

713
00:33:18,530 --> 00:33:19,860
it'd grow this tall now?

714
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:25,350
At the time, this was

715
00:33:25,460 --> 00:33:26,180
the only tree

716
00:33:26,180 --> 00:33:27,200
in our county.

717
00:33:31,250 --> 00:33:32,170
When Dad planted it,

718
00:33:32,170 --> 00:33:33,960
he surely couldn't have imagined

719
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:34,700
there would be

720
00:33:34,700 --> 00:33:35,850
other trees now too.

721
00:33:37,210 --> 00:33:38,070
I bet even this tree itself

722
00:33:38,070 --> 00:33:39,090
didn't expect

723
00:33:39,960 --> 00:33:41,810
to become...

724
00:33:44,220 --> 00:33:45,480
the King of Trees here.

725
00:33:46,250 --> 00:33:47,250
That's so cheesy.

726
00:33:48,330 --> 00:33:49,460
Good thing Zhuling's name

727
00:33:49,460 --> 00:33:50,660
wasn't chosen by you.

728
00:33:50,960 --> 00:33:51,740
Cheesy?

729
00:33:52,420 --> 00:33:54,350
Think about the vitality of a tree.

730
00:33:55,250 --> 00:33:57,180
It never chooses its destination.

731
00:33:57,200 --> 00:33:58,500
Once it takes root,

732
00:33:58,590 --> 00:33:59,850
it never moves an inch.

733
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:03,300
It entrusts its life to the earth,

734
00:34:03,590 --> 00:34:05,500
wind, rain, and sunlight.

735
00:34:06,680 --> 00:34:07,330
Do you know who in our family

736
00:34:07,330 --> 00:34:08,389
is most like a tree?

737
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:10,320
Me?

738
00:34:11,550 --> 00:34:12,500
It's Mom.

739
00:34:13,480 --> 00:34:14,400
You...

740
00:34:14,420 --> 00:34:15,699
You're like a rock.

741
00:34:19,070 --> 00:34:21,150
You're terrible at comforting people.

742
00:34:21,150 --> 00:34:22,880
What's wrong with being a rock?

743
00:34:25,030 --> 00:34:26,560
A rock can lie on a mountain,

744
00:34:27,130 --> 00:34:28,330
be buried in the soil,

745
00:34:28,860 --> 00:34:29,980
or rest in a river.

746
00:34:31,070 --> 00:34:32,690
With water flowing over it,

747
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:35,480
after years of washing and weathering,

748
00:34:35,590 --> 00:34:36,639
it'll become rounder

749
00:34:36,639 --> 00:34:37,770
and smoother,

750
00:34:38,190 --> 00:34:38,980
or change

751
00:34:39,630 --> 00:34:40,960
into some other shape.

752
00:34:48,190 --> 00:34:49,050
But you

753
00:34:49,860 --> 00:34:50,659
are still you.

754
00:35:00,210 --> 00:35:00,820
Bai Ju.

755
00:35:03,130 --> 00:35:03,650
Don't you have anything

756
00:35:03,650 --> 00:35:04,780
to ask me?

757
00:35:06,010 --> 00:35:06,690
About what?

758
00:35:10,730 --> 00:35:11,670
About Xinhai.

759
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:15,650
If you want to talk about it,

760
00:35:15,650 --> 00:35:17,050
you'll tell me yourself.

761
00:35:17,550 --> 00:35:18,610
I don't need to ask.

762
00:35:29,980 --> 00:35:30,540
I've already handed this photo over

763
00:35:30,540 --> 00:35:32,500
to the Provincial
Discipline Inspection Commission.

764
00:35:32,500 --> 00:35:34,210
They're taking it very seriously.

765
00:35:34,210 --> 00:35:36,120
We just need to know

766
00:35:36,150 --> 00:35:38,010
what exactly happened back then.

767
00:35:38,090 --> 00:35:39,300
Even a small piece of information

768
00:35:39,300 --> 00:35:40,720
could be a breakthrough.

769
00:35:42,710 --> 00:35:44,170
They just classified it as

770
00:35:44,170 --> 00:35:46,630
"picking quarrels and provoking trouble."

771
00:35:47,940 --> 00:35:48,870
What do you mean?

772
00:35:51,320 --> 00:35:52,190
I reported them

773
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:53,280
back then.

774
00:35:54,230 --> 00:35:55,030
Later,

775
00:35:55,130 --> 00:35:55,630
they caught

776
00:35:55,630 --> 00:35:56,900
the guy

777
00:35:56,930 --> 00:35:57,860
who broke my leg.

778
00:35:58,210 --> 00:35:59,300
But they only charged him with

779
00:35:59,300 --> 00:36:01,590
"picking quarrels and provoking trouble."

780
00:36:01,590 --> 00:36:02,760
Feng Keqing did it?

781
00:36:08,380 --> 00:36:09,260
Now

782
00:36:10,570 --> 00:36:11,190
I don't know

783
00:36:11,190 --> 00:36:12,080
how deep

784
00:36:12,110 --> 00:36:14,030
his connections go.

785
00:36:16,610 --> 00:36:17,420
Actually,

786
00:36:17,530 --> 00:36:18,930
compared to Feng Keqing,

787
00:36:19,570 --> 00:36:20,920
the one who shocked

788
00:36:21,010 --> 00:36:22,410
and disappointed me more

789
00:36:23,110 --> 00:36:24,310
was County Mayor Lin.

790
00:36:27,150 --> 00:36:27,810
Feng Keqing

791
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:28,500
was the one who

792
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:30,430
introduced me to County Mayor Lin.

793
00:36:31,960 --> 00:36:33,070
I gave him coal,

794
00:36:34,260 --> 00:36:35,440
and I even promised his son

795
00:36:35,440 --> 00:36:36,270
a job at Tengda

796
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:38,210
after graduation.

797
00:36:38,940 --> 00:36:39,440
Yes.

798
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:40,750
I admit

799
00:36:40,780 --> 00:36:42,400
I had selfish motives at the time.

800
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:44,480
But we should judge by actions,
not intentions, right?

801
00:36:44,480 --> 00:36:45,300
I believe

802
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:46,500
I can honestly say

803
00:36:46,530 --> 00:36:47,730
I did right

804
00:36:48,570 --> 00:36:49,700
by County Mayor Lin.

805
00:36:51,730 --> 00:36:52,550
But...

806
00:36:54,440 --> 00:36:56,040
after Tengda changed hands,

807
00:36:56,670 --> 00:36:57,640
Lin Jianshe

808
00:36:57,670 --> 00:36:59,170
still went to work there.

809
00:36:59,280 --> 00:37:00,300
Feng Keqing arranged it?

810
00:37:00,300 --> 00:37:01,830
Who else could it have been?

811
00:37:01,940 --> 00:37:02,680
Lin Jianshe

812
00:37:02,710 --> 00:37:04,070
went abroad not long after that.

813
00:37:04,070 --> 00:37:04,930
They said it was

814
00:37:04,940 --> 00:37:06,230
a company program

815
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:07,800
for talent development.

816
00:37:08,230 --> 00:37:09,570
Some talent.

817
00:37:15,340 --> 00:37:16,260
Things

818
00:37:16,370 --> 00:37:17,830
are really different now?

819
00:37:20,650 --> 00:37:21,150
Yes.

820
00:37:22,340 --> 00:37:23,130
The Provincial
Discipline Inspection Commission

821
00:37:23,130 --> 00:37:24,010
is paying close attention to this matter.

822
00:37:24,010 --> 00:37:24,760
They want to find out

823
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:25,890
who their backer is.

824
00:37:26,170 --> 00:37:27,010
You've provided us

825
00:37:27,010 --> 00:37:28,230
with a crucial lead.

826
00:37:54,030 --> 00:37:55,360
The transfer fee was...

827
00:37:55,820 --> 00:37:56,750
was 10,000 yuan?

828
00:37:59,320 --> 00:38:00,360
A company

829
00:38:01,460 --> 00:38:02,780
plus my leg—

830
00:38:03,630 --> 00:38:04,480
10,000 yuan.

831
00:38:05,600 --> 00:38:06,860
Ridiculous, isn't it?

832
00:38:12,300 --> 00:38:14,210
You know, a rock can wait

833
00:38:15,090 --> 00:38:16,070
hundreds of millions of years

834
00:38:16,070 --> 00:38:17,780
and produce something.

835
00:38:18,050 --> 00:38:19,230
But humans can't.

836
00:38:20,110 --> 00:38:20,510
Here.

837
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:22,360
Take this too.

838
00:38:23,300 --> 00:38:24,450
Both of them are yours.

839
00:38:24,450 --> 00:38:25,050
Take them.

840
00:38:26,530 --> 00:38:27,330
Manager Zhao,

841
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:30,070
would you be willing to go with me

842
00:38:30,070 --> 00:38:31,530
to the provincial capital

843
00:38:31,670 --> 00:38:32,730
as a whistleblower

844
00:38:33,030 --> 00:38:33,980
to report

845
00:38:34,610 --> 00:38:35,420
Lin Peisheng's connections from back then

846
00:38:35,420 --> 00:38:38,480
to the Provincial
Discipline Inspection Commission?

847
00:38:46,030 --> 00:38:46,650
Who?

848
00:38:50,460 --> 00:38:51,920
That guy is still alive?

849
00:38:56,820 --> 00:38:57,570
Got it.

850
00:38:59,530 --> 00:39:00,110
Then...

851
00:39:00,630 --> 00:39:01,560
when should I go?

852
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:04,440
Okay.

853
00:39:05,730 --> 00:39:06,380
Got it.

854
00:39:33,030 --> 00:39:33,690
In the back.

855
00:39:34,670 --> 00:39:35,530
Him in the back.

856
00:39:38,420 --> 00:39:38,990
Here!

857
00:39:41,570 --> 00:39:43,090
What's wrong?

858
00:39:46,050 --> 00:39:47,850
When will we get to the rest stop?

859
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:49,530
Didn't we just stop?

860
00:39:50,510 --> 00:39:51,860
Don't worry.

861
00:39:51,950 --> 00:39:53,150
We don't need a break.

862
00:39:53,880 --> 00:39:54,430
Later,

863
00:39:54,460 --> 00:39:56,190
Reporter Shao and I
will take turns driving.

864
00:39:56,190 --> 00:39:57,900
We'll reach the provincial capital soon.

865
00:39:57,900 --> 00:39:59,880
I want a break.

866
00:40:00,440 --> 00:40:01,370
Then go to sleep.

867
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:03,570
Well, just now...

868
00:40:03,570 --> 00:40:05,550
I drank a bit too much water.

869
00:40:05,650 --> 00:40:07,480
I drank quite a lot too.

870
00:40:08,070 --> 00:40:09,630
I'm older than you!

871
00:40:09,670 --> 00:40:10,910
When you get to my age,

872
00:40:10,940 --> 00:40:12,010
you'll understand.

873
00:40:12,010 --> 00:40:13,470
When you get older, you...

874
00:40:13,940 --> 00:40:15,340
you just can't hold it in.

875
00:40:17,740 --> 00:40:19,090
Quick, pull over.

876
00:40:20,510 --> 00:40:21,770
Manager Zhao, hang on.

877
00:40:21,820 --> 00:40:23,080
I'll pull over for you.

878
00:40:24,010 --> 00:40:24,710
No, no.

879
00:40:25,420 --> 00:40:26,680
There's no cover here.

880
00:40:27,090 --> 00:40:27,730
Well...

881
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:30,120
Some things you can hold,

882
00:40:30,510 --> 00:40:31,840
and some you just can't.

883
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:34,370
It's not that I can't hold it at all,

884
00:40:34,630 --> 00:40:36,510
but I can't hold everything either.

885
00:40:36,510 --> 00:40:37,340
Alright, alright.

886
00:40:37,340 --> 00:40:38,250
Well, don't worry.

887
00:40:38,250 --> 00:40:38,980
Just up ahead,

888
00:40:38,980 --> 00:40:40,110
there's a rest stop.

889
00:40:40,380 --> 00:40:41,780
Just hold it a bit longer.

890
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:43,860
Hurry, hurry.

891
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:11,030
No, thanks.

892
00:41:15,480 --> 00:41:17,500
The old man is quite particular.

893
00:41:20,240 --> 00:41:21,970
You think everyone is like you?

894
00:41:23,420 --> 00:41:24,510
What are you doing?

895
00:41:24,890 --> 00:41:26,220
Reporting to my leader.

896
00:41:27,320 --> 00:41:29,800
"Everything is going well on the road.

897
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:31,440
Remember to eat on time."

898
00:41:35,210 --> 00:41:37,190
You care so much about your leader.

899
00:41:37,270 --> 00:41:38,000
You have

900
00:41:38,030 --> 00:41:39,170
great eyesight.

901
00:41:40,110 --> 00:41:41,920
I can even see there's a car

902
00:41:42,010 --> 00:41:43,410
parked on that mountain.

903
00:41:48,820 --> 00:41:50,050
Is that a car?

904
00:41:50,460 --> 00:41:51,670
That black dot there.

905
00:41:52,780 --> 00:41:53,670
Look closely.

906
00:41:54,170 --> 00:41:55,230
Amazing, amazing.

907
00:42:00,110 --> 00:42:02,040
Why is Manager Zhao taking so long?

908
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:08,110
The signal is bad.

909
00:42:32,460 --> 00:42:33,330
Manager Zhao?

910
00:42:36,990 --> 00:42:37,820
Manager Zhao!

911
00:42:39,300 --> 00:42:40,090
Shao!

912
00:42:41,660 --> 00:42:42,460
Shao!

913
00:42:42,780 --> 00:42:43,340
Zhacuo!

914
00:42:43,630 --> 00:42:44,320
Zhacuo!

915
00:43:07,160 --> 00:43:08,390
Zhacuo!
